Lets Just Look at Character Ratings

Characters are rated on a likert scale, from 1 (very unfavorable) to 5 (very favorable). *Note that we dont have a good definition for what favorable really means.

jdat <- na.omit(jedi[,c(18:29)])
as.numeric.factor <- function(x) {as.numeric(levels(x))[x]}
factor_coerce <- function(x) {as.numeric.factor(factor(x))}
apply(jdat,2,factor_coerce)

Well we want to know which characters (questions) drive the most variability. Lets look at a quick PCA:

##Principal Components Analysis
pc1 <- prcomp(jdat)
plot(pc1$x[,1], pc1$x[,2], type = "n", main = "Principal Components")
text(pc1$x[,1], pc1$x[,2], labels = colnames(jdat))

biplot(pc1, var.axes = TRUE, col = c('gray80','red3'), xlim = c(-.18,.15))

summary(pc1) #suggests we'd need several factors
